# Created by the publish job's `Build npm packages` step (npm install +
# npm run build) before the engine runs cargo publish on the sibling
# Rust crate. Without this, cargo's workspace dirty-check trips on the
# untracked install state and aborts. Real consumers hitting the same
# pattern want the same gitignore in their repos; the engine should
# ideally pass --allow-dirty to cargo publish, but that's a separate
# engine-side fix.
node_modules/
package-lock.json
dist/
